<p>I use TextClock command in a home widget. No problem in KitKat but in Lollipop I don't found a way to display the month. I usually use MMM or MMMMM but in lollipop the result is something like this: 01/10/2015.</p>  <p>Why? Any idea? Thanks</p>  <p>this is my code:</p>  <pre><code>                           &lt;TextClock                            android:id="@+id/secondi"                            android:layout_width="wrap_content"                            android:layout_height="wrap_content"                            android:layout_alignParentRight="true"                            android:layout_alignTop="@+id/analogClock1"                            android:layout_marginRight="96dp"                            android:layout_marginTop="125dp"                            android:format12Hour="EEE, dd MMMM"                            android:format24Hour="EEE, dd MMMM"                            android:gravity="center_horizontal"                            android:lines="2"                            android:textColor="#e6e6e6"                            android:textSize="11dp"                            android:typeface="sans"                            android:width="45dp" /&gt; </code></pre>  <p>The same widget in a Kitkat phone display: "Thu, 01 October" in another lollipop phone "10/1/2015</p>